Instruction: Systematically test for a hidden wiring/configuration error by re‑assembling the system in different valid series orders. First, connect PSU → ctrl1 → ctrl2 → ctrl3 → ctrl4 → ctrl5 → ctrl6 → ctrl7 → ctrl8 → load and verify lamp operation; then, with power removed, permute the physical cubes while keeping the same *logical* order (e.g., swap the physical positions of two control modules but maintain logical numbering in the series) and check whether the lamp still lights in all cases. Any configuration in which individual subchains work but the full chain fails indicates that at least one pair of fast‑connection terminals is mismatched (a 12 V line from one cube mated to the 0 V line of another). Identify and note any cable pair(s) that must be cross‑connected to restore operation in the full chain.
